HEADWORD: Flews
<hw>Flews</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>The pendulous or
overhanging lateral parts of the upper lip of dogs, especially prominent
in hounds; -- called also <altname>chaps</altname>. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Bloodhound</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flex</ent>⟦br⟧
